--:_BLIGHTBURN_SICKNESS_INFORMATION|
    --&Affliction_Name|Blightburn Sickness
    --&Affliction_Level|9
    --&Affliction_Traits|Disease
    --&Affliction_Notes|Creatures native to the Black Desert are immune, as are creatures who are affected by blightburn sickness but recover from it. The target can't recover from the disease's drained or sickened condition except by magic. [br]The surest way to avoid contracting blightburn sickness is by wearing a blightburn ward, a piece of protective jewelry often found among urdefhans' gear or for sale in Shraen.
    --&Affliction_DC|32
    --&Affliction_Save_Type|Fortitude
    --&Affliction_Max_Duration|   
    --&Affliction_Stage_1|Drained 1 (Duration: 1 day)
    --&Affliction_Stage_2|Drained 1 and Sickened 1 (Duration: 1 day)
    --&Affliction_Stage_3|Drained 2 and Sickened 2 (Duration: 1 week)
    --&Affliction_Stage_4|Drained 3 and Sickened 3 (Duration: 1 month)
    --&Affliction_Stage_5|Increase Drained condition by 1 (Duration: 1 year)
    --&Affliction_Stage_6| 
    --^PRINT_AFFLICTION_DATA|

